%20well-protected%20organ%20in%20the%20human%20body%2C%20but%20it%20has%20a%20surprisingly%20high%20amount%20of%20microplastic%20pollution%2C%20according%20to%20a%20paper%20published%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%3Fh%3D43a32928a74914fe75cba887f26dc613e5fec42ef2f3a2df6864c1014b012a1d%26postID%3D679be9dce72cf8b4936592bb%26postSlug%3Dmicroplastics-human-brains-high-levels-2025-1%26site%3Dbi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.nature.com%252Farticles%252Fs41591-024-03453-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENature%20Medicine%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20Monday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20study%2C%20researchers%20examined%2052%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Fhuman-blood-microplastics%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebrain%20samples%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20autopsies%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eand%20found%20they%20contained%20seven%20to%2030%20times%20more%20microplastics%20and%20nanoplastics%20compared%20to%20kidney%20and%20liver%20samples.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20amount%20of%20plastic%20the%20researchers%20found%20in%20the%20average%20brain%20sample%20is%20about%20equivalent%20to%20a%20plastic%20spoon%2C%20according%20to%20lead%20author%20Matthew%20Campen.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20the%20measurement%20methods%20are%20still%20being%20developed.%20%26quot%3BWe're%20working%20hard%20to%20get%20to%20a%20very%20precise%20estimate%2C%26quot%3B%20Campen%20said%20in%20a%20press%20conference%20on%20Monday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22899c6dd7-586d-4f0f-9cf5-719deecf91fc%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20this%20means%20for%20neurological%20health%20is%20unclear%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20brain%20samples%20were%20taken%20from%20the%20prefrontal%20cortex%2C%20which%20controls%20behavior%20and%20is%20involved%20with%20decision-making.%20Most%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicroplastics-found-in-penis-muscles-for-the-first-time-study-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eplastics%20found%20were%20nano-sized%20shards%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20flakes%20of%20polyethylene%2C%20which%20is%20used%20in%20plastic%20bags%2C%20plastic%20food%20wrapping%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcategory%2Fmicroplastics%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eplastic%20water%20bottles%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20unclear%20what%20effect%20this%20may%20have%20on%20neurological%20health.%20In%20the%20study%2C%20the%2012%20people%20with%20documented%20dementia%20had%20higher%20levels%20of%20nanoplastics%20in%20their%20brain%20samples%20compared%20to%20samples%20from%20people%20without%20dementia.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20cannot%20say%2C%20from%20this%20study%2C%20that%20micro-nanoplastics%20are%20causing%20dementia%2C%26quot%3B%20Jaime%20Ross%2C%20an%20assistant%20professor%20of%20neuroscience%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Rhode%20Island%20who%20wasn't%20involved%20with%20the%20study%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Falzheimers-vs-dementia%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDementia%20patients%3C%2Fa%3E%20often%20have%20impaired%20blood-brain%20barriers%2C%20meaning%20the%20elevated%20levels%20of%20micro-nanoplastics%20may%20have%20been%20a%20symptom%20and%20not%20a%20cause%20of%20the%20disease.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20it's%20going%20to%20be%20challenging%20for%20clinicians%20to%20distill%20the%20important%20parts%20of%20this%20down%20for%20patients%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Campen%2C%20a%20toxicologist%20and%20professor%20of%20pharmaceutical%20sciences%20at%20the%20University%20of%20New%20Mexico.%20%26quot%3BThe%20big%20thing%20that%20patients%20need%20to%20hear%20is%20that%20it's%20not%20known%20that%20there%20are%20health%20effects%20that%20are%20caused%20by%20the%20plastics%20at%20this%20point.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMicroplastics%20have%20been%20found%20in%20many%20parts%20of%20the%20human%20body%2C%20including%20the%20heart%2C%20liver%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicroplastics-found-in-human-testicles-what-to-do-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etesticles%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20breast%20milk.%20Experts%20don't%20fully%20understand%20the%20health%20impact%2C%20though%20some%20studies%20have%20linked%20microplastics%20to%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicroplastics-risks-heart-attack-stroke-study-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20heart%20disease%2C%20strokes%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.medicalnewstoday.com%2Farticles%2Fmicroplastics-in-testicles-may-play-a-role-in-male-infertility-study-suggests%23How-do-microplastics-influence-infertility%3F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20low%20sperm%20count%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Researchers%20are%20also%20investigating%20whether%20they%20play%20a%20role%20in%20the%20risk%20of%20developing%20certain%20types%20of%20cancers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20wouldn't%20surprise%20me%20if%20micro-nanoplastics%20are%20affecting%20us.%20We%20just%20don't%20know%20to%20what%20extent%2C%20yet%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Ross%2C%20who%20co-authored%20a%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mdpi.com%2F1422-0067%2F24%2F15%2F12308%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20paper%3C%2Fa%3E%20published%20in%202023%20that%20found%20behavioral%20changes%20and%20brain%20inflammation%20in%20mice%20after%20they%20drank%20microplastic-polluted%20water%20for%20three%20weeks%20straight.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22968b01ba-4a16-4469-a183-e82780c97f6e%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20brain%20has%20a%20protective%20barrier%20that%20should%20protect%20us%20against%20microplastics%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EUnlike%20the%20kidney%2C%20liver%2C%20and%20other%20organs%2C%20the%20human%20brain%20has%20a%20protective%20filter%20called%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicroplastics-discovered-in-human-blood-for-the-first-time-2022-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eblood-brain%20barrier%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20blocks%20many%20harmful%20pathogens%20and%20toxins.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECampen%20said%20it's%20unclear%20from%20his%20research%20why%20so%20many%20nanoplastics%20are%20managing%20to%20cross%20the%20blood-brain%20barrier%2C%20but%20the%20brain's%20high%20proportion%20of%20lipids%2C%20or%20fats%2C%20likely%20plays%20a%20role.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you've%20ever%20cleaned%20a%20Tupperware%20bowl%20that%20had%20bacon%20grease%20or%20butter%20in%20it%2C%20it%20takes%20a%20lot%20of%20soap%20and%20hot%20water.%20It's%20really%20hard%20to%20get%20the%20plastics%20and%20fats%20apart.%20We%20think%20that's%20part%20of%20this%20process%2C%26quot%3B%20Campen%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22ce418b04-e307-4958-aaa0-46cbfd6225bb%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20silver%20lining%20is%20that%20microplastics%20may%20not%20accumulate%20in%20the%20human%20body%20over%20time%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20latest%20study%20didn't%20show%20higher%20levels%20of%20micro%20and%20nanoplastics%20in%20older%20brains%20compared%20to%20younger%20brains%2C%20suggesting%20our%20bodies%20can%20pass%20enough%20of%20these%20plastics%20in%20our%20feces%20to%20prevent%20buildup.%20%26quot%3BSo%20we're%20not%20just%20accumulating%20these%20over%20time%2C%20over%20our%20lifetimes%2C%26quot%3B%20Campen%20said.%20More%20research%20is%20needed%20to%20confirm%20that%20finding.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20study%20did%2C%20however%2C%20find%20an%20increase%20in%20micro%20and%20nanoplastics%20in%20brain%20and%20liver%20samples%20taken%20from%20individuals%20who%20died%20in%202024%20compared%20to%202016.%20Campen%20said%20this%20increase%20is%20likely%20due%20to%20the%20increase%20in%20plastics%20in%20the%20environment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20significant%20because%20it%20suggests%20that%20if%20we%20were%20to%20reduce%20environmental%20contamination%20with%20microplastics%2C%20the%20levels%20of%20human%20exposure%20would%20also%20decrease%2C%26quot%3B%20Tamara%20Galloway%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20ecotoxicology%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Exeter%20who%20was%20not%20involved%20in%20the%20research%2C%20said%20in%20a%20statement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMicroplastics%20are%20inescapable%20%E2%80%94%20they're%20in%20our%20food%2C%20air%2C%20water%2C%20and%20trash.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20can%20reduce%20your%20exposure%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fexpert-how-i-keep-baby-family-safe-toxic-plastic-microplastics-2023-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewashing%20your%20hands%20before%20you%20eat%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20removing%20plastic%20from%20food%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicroplastic-reduce-exposure-consumption-at-home-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebefore%20microwaving%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20avoiding%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthousands-of-chemicals-entering-human-bodies-from-food-packaging-study-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edrinking%20from%20plastic%20bottles%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicroplastics-human-brains-high-levels-2025-1%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1738615691000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F679beabfeb4be2fff9a30221%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicroplastics-human-brains-high-levels-2025-1%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Researchers%20studied%20samples%20of%20human%20brains%20and%20found%20high%20levels%20of%20microplastics%2C%20but%20it's%20unclear%20how%20they%20slip%20past%20the%20blood-brain%20barrier.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22jmcgrath%40insider.com%20(Jenny%20McGrath%2CJessica%20Orwig)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A131%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicroplastics-human-brains-h